Document: CSGSphere3D  
Path: godot/classes/class_csgsphere3d.rst  
Summary: Properties and their descriptions for the CSGSphere3D class, including material, radial segments, radius, rings, and smooth faces settings.  

Material: material. Default: none. Set via set_material(Material), get via get_material(). The material used to render the sphere.  
radial_segments (int): Number of vertical slices for the sphere. Default: 12. Set via set_radial_segments(int), get via get_radial_segments().  
radius (float): Radius of the sphere. Default: 0.5. Set via set_radius(float), get via get_radius().  
rings (int): Number of horizontal slices for the sphere. Default: 6. Set via set_rings(int), get via get_rings().  
smooth_faces (bool): If true the normals of the sphere are set to give a smooth effect making the sphere seem rounded. If false the sphere will have a flat shaded look. Default: true. Set via set_smooth_faces(bool), get via get_smooth_faces().